section.para:
This module is useful for monitoring the progress of &sip;
call transfers (blind and attended) and taking action based
on transfer success or failure.

example.programlisting:
...
route {
    if (is_method("REFER")) {
        if (handle_refer("$hdr(Refer-To)")) {
            sl_send_reply(202, "Accepted");
        } else {
            sl_send_reply(500, "Internal Error");
        }
    }
}
...

...
route {
    if (is_method("REFER")) {
        if (is_present_hf("Replaces")) {
            if (handle_attended_refer("$hdr(Refer-To)", "$hdr(Replaces)")) {
                xlog("L_INFO", "attended transfer: replaces=$var(refer_replaces)\n");
                sl_send_reply(202, "Accepted");
            }
        } else {
            if (handle_refer("$hdr(Refer-To)")) {
                sl_send_reply(202, "Accepted");
            }
        }
    }
}
...

...
route {
    if (is_method("NOTIFY")) {
        # Parse sipfrag body for status code
        if (handle_notify("$ci", "$var(sipfrag_code)")) {
            sl_send_reply(200, "OK");
        } else {
            sl_send_reply(481, "Subscription does not exist");
        }
    }
}
...

listitem.para:
1  - status found;
$var(refer_status) set to the status
string.

example.programlisting:
...
route[check_transfer] {
    if (refer_status("$ci")) {
        xlog("L_INFO", "transfer $ci status: $var(refer_status)\n");
        if ($var(refer_status) == "success") {
            # Transfer completed successfully
        }
        if ($var(refer_status) == "failed") {
            # Transfer failed - take recovery action
        }
    }
}
...

...
route[send_transfer_notify] {
    # Prepare the NOTIFY
    send_refer_notify("$ci", "200");

    # Use the prepared values to send via t_uac_dlg
    xlog("L_INFO", "sending NOTIFY cseq=$var(refer_notify_cseq) "
        "body=$var(refer_notify_body)\n");
}
...

...
route {
    if (is_method("REFER")) {
        if (!check_transfer_target("$hdr(Refer-To)")) {
            sl_send_reply(403, "Transfer target not allowed");
            exit;
        }
        handle_refer("$hdr(Refer-To)");
        sl_send_reply(202, "Accepted");
    }
}
...
